WEBVTT

00:01.460 --> 00:04.027
I'm telling you, if xenon emits
ultraviolet light,

00:04.029 --> 00:06.430
then those dark matter
discoveries must be wrong.

00:06.431 --> 00:08.432
Yes, well, if we lived
in a world

00:08.433 --> 00:10.468
where slow-moving xenon
produced light,

00:10.469 --> 00:11.702
then you'd be correct.

00:11.703 --> 00:13.237
Also, pigs would fly,

00:13.238 --> 00:15.072
my derriere would produce
cotton candy,

00:15.073 --> 00:18.676
and <i>The Phantom Menace</i>
would be a timeless classic.

00:18.677 --> 00:19.877
Oh, you're so arrogant.

00:19.878 --> 00:21.178
If you were a superhero,

00:21.179 --> 00:22.947
your name would be
Captain Arrogant.

00:22.948 --> 00:25.116
And you know
what your superpower would be?

00:25.117 --> 00:26.617
Arrogance.

00:26.618 --> 00:28.886
You're wrong again.

00:28.887 --> 00:34.725
If my superpower were arrogance,
my name would be Dr. Arroganto.

00:34.726 --> 00:37.862
I love watching Raj and Sheldon
try to work together.

00:37.863 --> 00:39.864
Yeah, it's like
if Alien and Predator decided

00:39.865 --> 00:43.300
to go partners
in a Jamba Juice.

00:43.301 --> 00:45.169
Has it occurred to you
you're missing the big picture?

00:45.170 --> 00:47.271
If you look at neutron
scattering data...
Oh, Penny?

00:47.272 --> 00:48.339
Penny?
What's up?

00:48.340 --> 00:50.141
Nothing. I just wanted

00:50.142 --> 00:52.409
to make Raj stop talking.

00:52.410 --> 00:54.311
No, no, no.

00:54.312 --> 00:55.980
He won. Suck it up.

00:55.981 --> 00:58.415
Well, I'd ask you guys
if you want dessert,

00:58.416 --> 01:00.618
but I know Sheldon doesn't
eat dessert on Tuesdays.

01:00.619 --> 01:03.087
And even if Raj wanted
something, he couldn't tell me.

01:03.088 --> 01:04.321
Howard won't order anything,

01:04.322 --> 01:06.490
but he will come up
with some sort of skeevy comment

01:06.491 --> 01:08.125
involving the words pie
or cheesecake.

01:08.126 --> 01:10.327
And Leonard's
lactose intolerant,

01:10.328 --> 01:11.729
so he can't eat anything here

01:11.730 --> 01:13.264
without his intestines
blowing up

01:13.265 --> 01:14.498
like a balloon animal.

01:14.499 --> 01:17.268
Hang on a second.

01:17.269 --> 01:18.836
I could have the fruit platter.

01:18.837 --> 01:19.804
You want the fruit platter?

01:19.805 --> 01:21.338
Does it have melon
on it?
Yeah.

01:21.339 --> 01:22.807
No, I can't eat melon.

01:24.075 --> 01:25.342
Oh, Howard,
heads up.

01:25.343 --> 01:28.512
Your ex-girlfriend just
came in for her shift.

01:28.513 --> 01:30.347
When was the last time
you saw her?

01:30.348 --> 01:31.949
Oh, not since we broke up.

01:31.950 --> 01:35.085
Wow. How am I going
to play this?

01:35.086 --> 01:37.154
Sophisticated and relaxed?

01:37.155 --> 01:38.556
Friendly, noncommittal?

01:38.557 --> 01:40.357
Cold and distant?

01:43.628 --> 01:45.062
Hi, guys.
Hey.

01:45.063 --> 01:46.831
Hello.

01:46.832 --> 01:51.035
I see you decided to go
with pathetic and frightened.

01:51.036 --> 01:53.637
It's one of his best moves.

